this is an indepth review scroll down to the conclusion if youre short on time or want the bottom line but if you are looking at this game i highly recommend reading all of this introduction warframe is a wonderfully unique and constantly evolving very social freetoplay third person shooter with a focus on cooperative player versus enemy combat nearly every mission is procedurally generated each time you load it and it will be a specified game mode with a set objective there are 4 factions plus a neutral faction mostly composed of fauna to fight against with tons of interesting enemies there many customization options for players there are player skins color palettes with 90 colors each decals bobbleheads helmets and more you can have a hot pink ninja with a moustache movember only and scarf blowing kisses if you so desire it is quite grindcentric but it is excellent at what it does the grind is a design choice and not a symptom of not having enough game content so dont be scared off by that the business model for microtransactions is very fair purchasing weapons will generally not give you a signifcant advantage outside of some timesaving there is no paytowin here what you get for purchasing the premium currency with real money is the ability to skip some of the grind or random elements cosmetic items and likely the most important are item slots you only have a tiny number of slots to begin with and you will need to sell your old gear to acquire new gear or get platinum to buy slots possible to sell rare items without paying a penny you are also given some platinum to start with you can obtain almost 100% of the gameplay content without paying a dime but if you get hooked on this game fair warning you will probably want to spend some cash im not rich by any means whatsoever but ive spent a large percentage of my average entertainment budget on this game and i look back with no regrets to get the same amount of entertainment out of going to the movies as i have gotten playing this game i would have to spend around $750010000 usd the bottom line in warframe is that you will be progressing at your desired pace and with your own goal which may be one of the following do i want to complete every mission do i want to be the best pvper do i want to acquire every weapon in the game do i want to break the weekly record in survivaldefense modes do i want to piece together the game lore and write my own story do i want to find a tightknit community and help construct an amazing clan hangout with tech research obstacle courses statues displaying clan achievements literal zen gardens and more do i want to acquire every one of the hundreds of mods more or less lootable trading cards you jam in your gear to change your ability range gun damage fire rate move speed knockdown resistance slide distance wall run cost and much more the choice is yours in warframe the developers are also extremely involved with the community if a change goes out that the whole community dislikes even if the developers still think the revision is correct they will listen to the players and change it anyway and roll back the change within 24 hours sometimes they have contests q&as devstreams and more there are global operations that take place every few weeks that reward players with exclusive items for things such as sabotaging a mobilizing space army or preventing a faction from discovering something that would make them too strong they really stay in touch with fans on a personal level the hotfixes are announced in realtime ingame by the enigmatic and hysterical redtext whose dialogue makes you feel like youre a personal friend of the developers never have i seen a developer care more about their game and the players i started playing roughly a year and a half ago after update 7 the game had maybe 30 weapons total all of them being this weapon shoots more bullets faster than this weapon and has a bigger clip size on basically one tile set the game is now on update 152 and has 13 beautiful and varied tilesets weapons ranging from rocket launchers to poison cloud launchers to chemical acidthrowers to freezerays and a massive oversized heman sword is it for me if youre a casual gamer you dont have to grind much and you can mostly flow through the missions and play with your buddies and just take it easy if youd like there are lots of newplayerfriendly tutorials and explanations that have been added that make it easier if youre a hardcore gamer there is plenty to offer if you dont mind a selfdirected grind as of this writing there are 178 weapons 28 warframes 11 companions 253 mission nodes 428 mods and more with content added almost each week once you rank an item up to the max level 30 you can use forma to improve your item and reset it to rank 0 to repeat the process with this system you can endlessly improve upon your weapons and warframes as much as you wish and do harder and harder content and do longer survivals and defenses there is more to do but ive covered the big goals here conclusion warframe is one of my personal favorite games i very highly reccomend it if you can tolerate some repetition and you like fun action games positive fresh concepts space ninjas with an easternstyle code of honor serve the mysterious lotus the player is intended to drive their own story some decisions can be made to shape this fun fluid gameplay that never gets boring there are playstyles to suit every player and many maneuvers such as wallrunning flipping rolling blocking counterattacking and sliding massive amount of warframes weapons mods and missions to keep you busy for hundreds of hours incredibly involved developer that addresses community concerns and improves the game weekly fair microtransactions no paytowin cooperative mostly friendly community as with every game there are some jerkstrolls wellexecuted clan system that lets you construct a central hub and hangout for you and your friends negative most items are built through accumulating the same dozen or so materials after mission progression ends this process becomes repetetive some items require repeating the same mission type over and over to get a certain weapon piece as a reward a small amount of weapons and one warframe are acquirable only through randomly generated onehour alert missions this can be frustrating if an alert you need occurs while you are asleep global operations are timesensitive so if you go on vacation or cant log on for some time there is a chance you may miss an operation with an exclusive item for the reward there are several eventexclusive items that will never be available again this may bother some perfectionists very difficult to acquire cosmetic customizations and item slots without paying money many minor bugs and many bugfixes result in a game of whackamole an incomplete plot makes it so theres no compelling goal yet but plot is being added in chunks slowly multiplayer is peertopeer and the network code is a bit buggy which often means slightlytomoderately laggy games endgame for veterans currently  in general amounts to collecting warframes and weapons and making your gear stronger this will likely change in the future playeraligned factions have recently been added to help with this that provide rewards only available for siding with that syndicate and earning experience while having their sigil equipped
recommended
warframe is a refreshing blend of fps rpglike progression and mmo interactivity my average warframe session plays as follows the game opens up to an overlay of the solar system the options from here are fairly analogous to that of diablo iii from here you have access to your equipment inventory crafting market with both ingame and out of game currency items clan chat and friends list unique to warframe is the solar map it features high interactivity allowing you to drill down two levels of detail selecting a planetplanetoid allows you to see all available mission in that system upon hovering on a mission the map shows the mission type faction and level of difficulty presented in the mission there are various ways to run missions but the most commonly used is online in this mode you matchmake with other players wanting to run the same mission once matchmaking begins you can either select play now to begin the mission after a short countdown or simply wait for at least one other person to join before the countdown begins automatically if you are running though a mission and its not yet full4 players max and the objective is still incomplete players will be able to drop in midmission the more players working together the higher the experience and reward payout progression in warfame is accomplished through a couple different systems your account has a rank it begins at 1 and slowly builds up as you play through the game progressing to the next rank requires completing a trial accessed by clicking on the xp bar on the main menu once its full and flashing certain weapons require a certain account rank or mastery rank your warframe weapons and carrier has a level these cap at 30 as these are raised your health shields stamina engery and damage increase each level provides the respective equipment an additional amount of capacity for mods each new weapon and new warframe that you level helps build your mastery and is proven to be the quickest way to progress each mod drains capacity but gives an upgrade these are both increased my fusing the mod to higher levels this offers near limitless upgradeability to your frame and weapons of choice as you progress though the games content you will collect more mods along the way allowing you to further customize your build to your needs chasing difficult to find mods and upgrading them to their full potential is a challenge in and of itself
