warframe is a thirdperson shooter similar in style to mass effect 3s multiplayer component you and a squad of up to three other players take on missions throughout the solar system to acquire loot in order to take on tougher missions for better loot a variety of special powers and an almost comically large selection of weapons are available to aid you in your quest along with cards which modify the properties and abilities of your warframe and weapons notably the game does not have a cover system with the developers opting for faster gameplay this choice is further evidenced by the parkourlike elements of wallrunning and vaulting smoothly over ledges and containers the game is a work in progress with frequent updates aiming to resolve bugs refine mechanics and add content par for the course as freetoplay games tend to go i would like to see more context provided for the actions undertaken by players ingame and some players will be turned off by the grind necessary to craft additional warframes and weapons a few technical issues such as crashes and networking issues also afflict a minority of users though thankfully these seem to be isolated problems these slight criticisms have not stopped me from enjoying the considerable time ive spent with the game however bottom line warframe is a concentrated dose of wish fulfillment if you like the idea of being a space ninja this game will probably entertain you for at least a couple dozen hours if you like grinding for item upgrades it may hold your interest considerably longer for the entry price of free its easy to recommend at least giving it a spin
