ill be honest i love this game love it to pieces you on the other hand may have a very different opinion i would normally say to do a lot of indepth research before making a commitment to any mmo but considering warframe is free i would say that all you need is a light brush over of what the in my opinion pros and cons of warframe are before trying it yourself pros free very intense action addictive very immersive for a 3rd person game beutiful atmosphere and world design with decent graphics interesting lore that is slowly revealed by community events and progression very good administrative team updates on a regular basis great customization of your arsenal everything necessary to the experience can be done without ingame currency platinum runs very smoothly even on the lowest end computers very helpful and friendly community trading system you can even trade for ingame currency not paytowin cons not friendly to the impatient long wait times for crafting slow progression very repetitivegrindy missions are clones of eachother with different graphics or gimmicks thrown in big pay wall as far as anything not essential to the experiance vanity exp multipliers credit boosts faster crafting etc buggy as all hell default settings are awful motion blur motion blur d balancing is off as far as weapons these are as far as i can tell the major pros and cons of warframe in conclusion warframe is a very satisfying and addictive game for those who are into fastpaced action that makes you feel like a complete badass and although it is not essential i would suggest laying down about 20 or 40 bucks or your regional equivalent just for convenience sake but please before putting any money down play the game for at least a day or two just to evaluate whether it is something you would truly enjoy thanks for reading i hope this was helpful
