fires seven beams of continuous biochemical energy which instantly corrode any surface they contact the phage is an infested shotgun researched in the clan bio lab with prerequisite being mutagen mass research it requires a mastery rank of 6 to build and comes with one  dash polarity slot note that its damage is viral not corrosive as the description implies as the codex description says it fires seven tentacleiike beams in a wide spread which move toward the center when you zoom there will always be a central beam while the others are emitted from glowing fingers three on each side of the weapons front without focusing targets to the side of the spread actually get hit by more beams when focused the resultant cluster of beams is about the size of your warframes head not pinpoint accurate but enough to land headshots on grineer the reload is quite unique the weapons fingers wriggle and it makes something akin to purring while you reload weapon mechanics the phage uses ammo very slowly id estimate it at one ammo per second of continuous fire that makes it more efficient than other continuous weapons though the decreased rate of shotgun ammo drop balances it out its focus can be tweaked depending on what youre up against  rarely do you want to fire the gun unfocused holding down the trigger lets you keep the current focus level without zooming in interrupting your fire in any way will unfocus the phage this means landing after a jump getting knocked down etc i found that you can walk off small steps without interrupting the fire so its not that bad i prefer leaving it at a semifocused wider cone of fire instead of the fully focused setting in most cases so i can sweep hallways and take out light units it feels like a hybrid between the ignis and the synapse  not as good as either in their optimal roles but very versatile the focus is a big issue for most users it will take time to get used to despite being a shotgun my personal tests using vay hek as a target havent resulted in any damage dropoff over range however this weapon is designed for closer range combat than the synapse  the slight spread of the beams at max focus means that you cant land fulldamage hits on small moving targets at range weapon build the phage is a slowerkilling weapon because of its focus time i would recommend a potato if you intend to use it as an actual primary it has a long delay before the spread approaches usable levels this is my build no forma point blank boosts base damage hells chamber adds additional beams to the phage  at max rank each finger will have an additional beam if you have them blaze and accelerated blast fire rate boosts rate of ammo consumption on continuous weapons but also increases damage add an elemental mod that fits in the dash  polarity slot before adding on hells chamber because itll boost damage more efficiently toxic barrage  im low on forma and this is more efficient than other elemental mod for damage vicious spread increases the initial spread of the beams it does not slow down the focus time of the phage and increases damage since its unfocused mode is awkward anyway go for it builds thanks to umonkrag for writing up elemental optimizations for factions i usually dont bother changing loadouts at all so im pretty bad when it comes to maxing out damage point blank hells chamber blaze and accelerated blast are staples of a shotgun build accelerateds puncture damage is calculated like elemental damage and its fire rate is good on any gun besides the tigris vicious spread is also pretty good for reasons i mentioned above tainted shell cuts down on the phages initial spread but also immensely impacts weapon damage output and is a very expensive mod to max i do not personally recommend this mod  making the beams narrow enough to be functional will also reduce damage output by 50% or more grineer radiation  viral damage has a 75% bonus against grineer flesh and radiation has a 75% bonus against alloy armor which grineer heavies use blaze  charged shell  incendiary coat corpus magnetic damage rips through shields chilling grasp  charged shell put these mods before blaze so the fire damage doesnt try to combine with anything void corrosive  cold makes short work of shields as well as heavy gunners toxic barrage  charged shell  chilling grasp add contagious spread if you didnt get taintedvicious spread infested gas balances out the viral penalty and the phages spread takes out light infested easily contagious spread  blaze  incendiary coat seeking force may be useful as itll basically be a beamshooting ignis at half focus however its main strength is very high damage output without burning through your ammo too quickly in conclusion im preferential to infested weapons and shotguns so this may be a bit biased i love versatility in a weapon and not just the one size fits all method the phages damage spread control is amazingly fun letting me clear mobs of mooks as well as that napalm standing in the doorway i wish it didnt unfocus instantly though this thread on the warframe forums got a dev comment and they are looking into possibly changing the way the unfocus works that said it is not a shotgun as much as it is a jackofalltrades continuous weapon despite its high damage output the long focus time means that when youre using the phage you cant take out a higherlevel threat instantly which might get you killed instead when im talking about higherlevel threat im talking about things that a potatoed soma has trouble with this is not a mustpotato weapon if you like it it will certainly deserve a potato though its a viable alternative to the more standard endgame primaries offering more variety without causing power creep with 65 mod points to play with i can take out level 1520 corpus in a few seconds without focusing its strong and feels fun but its also really awkward seeing tentacles everywhere and given that de doesnt release weapons this strong all the time phages are going to be common sights for quite a while edit tested things with full vicious spread added a little more commentary adjusted
