warframe uses an interesting combat style that includes the use of maneuvers like wallrunning and walljumping that add to the skills one can have in combat these maneuvers are complemented by the large assortment of weapons that range from traditional weapons in shooter games like assault rifles and pistols to weapons like bows and throwing stars that have been upgraded to fit the futuristic scifi theme of the game one thing that must be noted about this impressive arsenal is that while one must pay money to buy ingame currency platinum to buy most weapons and warframes these same items can be just as easily built through the purchase of blueprints in the ingame market using credits earned from completing missions or by using blueprints found during missions i am not normally the type to pay in places where it is not needed so having this option appealed greatly to me on a negative note i feel that at this point the stages and enemies are overly uniform with not enough variation between planets and individual stages though at this point there have been changes made to some of the stages and enemies and i assume that more individualism will be seen between them especially considering that at the point that i am writing this the game is still in beta also the fact that the stages are generated differently each time it is played helps to keep it from seeming too much the same as well as keeping it fresh instead of being able to just memorize stages i have enjoyed my experiences with warframe so far and i would recommend it to others who may be on the fence about playing this actionfilled game
