a wonderful and inventive action fourplayer coop tps and a welcome breath of fresh air in a gaming environment previously dominated by first person shooters and call of dutylikes fastpaced gunplay and creative parkourlike acrobatics coupled with alien and exotic character and creature design give warframe refreshing 3d gameplay and aestetics without overly gimmicky or cartoony elements sadly flow can easily be interrupted by gamebreaking bugs glitches and server errors that seem to double with each patch and game update and the game lacks many features one might expect in an mmo such as a trading system and auction house the game can also feel a bit grindy at times with the need to farm the same areas multiple times to complete an item in the games crafting system warframe is f2p and gets all its revenue from the ingame cash shop where you can purchase options to further customize your warframe items to boost your abilities and new weapons and warframes thankfully all items in the cash shop are also available in game through mission so the game has adopted a paytogrindless system despite the many flaws of the game which is still in open beta warframe is a promising new game i would highly reccomend for anyone looking for a new and unique style of play with their friends there are opportunities for both the hardcore numbercruncher and the casual gamer and these arent mutually exclusive the wide variety of warframes weapons and abilities available to the player make warframe a highly customizable and genuinely enjoyable experience for actionloves of all types and honestly who doesnt want to wallrun across a room chop a robots head off and then burn his buddy alive with your mind space ninjas
