recommended
first and foremost warframe is a fastpaced thirdperson freetoplay shooter that is set thousands of years in the future so it does have a big scifi element to it there is a focus on cooperative gameplay but it is viable to play alone and with the recent pvp revamp coop isnt the only thing to do freetoplay may scare some people off but i have to say this is a game that does it right microtransactions do exist but everything in the game can be earned through playing the game albeit at a slower pace than simply buying it outright before i would say the only exception to this would be inventory slots and cosmetics but since trading was introduced those exceptions quickly disappeared leaving the system a true payforconvenience one instead of a paytowin one the gameplay is fast fluid sometimes a little choatic and easy to learn yet has some depth to it the movement system itself will be changing soon but at the moment it is also easy to learn except for a couple of mechanics that arent immediately apparent such as coptering and wallflinging but these are things that are picked up quickly as you learn theres a lot of customization in the game as well allowing you to choose from a variety of different warframes weapons and companions as well as how they look on top of that you can tweak their effectiveness through the use of the mod card system allowing for quite a few different playstyles the game isnt without its issues though such as parts of the grind the tutorial and the state of endgame as a freetoplay game it does have grind so if youre the kind that hates grinding you may be turned away by this and yes since its all rng it can be terrible at times but it isnt on par with the kind of grinding you would see in korean rpgs the tutorial is rather long and drawnout and leaves some things unexplained or arent explained very well i recommend asking around for help in the first relay social hubs or looking at the warframe wiki [warframewikiacom] for anything you need to know while region chat should be left as a last resort endgame is probably warframes weakest point as its either collecting everything or going for as long as you can in endless missions while waiting for the next event to pop up but with the addition of raids and pvp those are probably going to become a part of it as well for the better since there isnt a real defined endgame youre free to make your own of course that is all my own opinion all in all warframe is a fun freetoplay third person shooter that has eaten up more than a lot of my time and i recommend at least giving it a try what is there to lose its free
