recommended
i want to start out by saying that unlike a lot of reviews this will be a critical examination of the game and its mechanics i do not wish to bathe it in praise nor cut it down at the knees i wish only to be critical it will be long and unlike all these joke reviews lol i cut a guy in half 1010 it will hopefully clarify just what this fairly complicated game is all about i recommend this game but let me say that my recommendation comes with many qualifications it is these qualifications that have caused me to form a very strong opinion very early in my gameplay experience luckily the developers of this game are quite intelligent and responsive and are always looking for ways to improve the game warframe is a free to play coop thirdperson action shooter on the evolution engine and it looks really pretty thats about everything i need to mention about the engine or it would be if the game wasnt so buggy fortunately the developers have decent priorities when it comes to supporting the game and they fix their bugs about as often as can be expected some people will have really bad luck getting warframe to run when i started playing i was not one of them first impressions were good combat was reliably fun and the wallrunning flippy combo movement serves to improve combat flow rather than feel arbitrarily shoehorned in like many other games with this kind of movement system the premise is simple do missions to unlock more missions to do and while youre at it experiment with some of the hundreds of unique weapons how you go about this is my first huge qualification playing the game solo can be near impossible at times you will want to join up with friends or random players on most missions because solo play has been specifically balanced to be unenjoyable for players just starting out luckily this isnt a dealbreaker but it might make your first dozen hours a little frustrating this brings me nicely to my next point which is that the community of players is far too small most of the time you will be unable to find a squad willing to do your missions as most players are too busy farming specific bosses or events once again this can be remedied by having friends who play with you but a majority of missions are often ghosttowns in public matchmaking the game isnt really driven by quests theres only a few real quests in total and they mostly serve as story expansion or advanced tutorials for mechanics you probably couldnt figure out without some outside intervention in fact the game is so poorly explained sometimes that i found myself guessing what interface buttons did on occasion and being completely surprised when they did something else entirely luckily the developers are making large stride in improving the quality of life in this game and unlike most free to play developers cough cough planetside 2 cough they actually listen to their playerbase and make attempts to assuage the largest complaints you also dont level up in the traditional sense leveling up only increases your pool of available mod points for the piece of equipment that leveled up you place mods on your equipment keeping in mind the limited capacity and you try to be efficient about it upgrading mods is yet another process whose intricacies are lost on anyone not paying careful attention youll want to keep a few good weapons and make them even more powerful through special items completely earnable without need of real life money purchases regardless all equips cap out at level 30 and youll want to swap out to another weapon once you do because leveling up weapons is the fastest way to level up your profiles mastery rank which unlocks further items weapons trades and other things so once youve wrapped your head around all of that recall that this is a free to play game meaning the developers have to make some money somehow aside from aesthetic purchases the marketplace sells additional slots for weapons and warframes meaning you start out with very few slots this isnt unreasonable but my logic is they wouldnt limit the amount of slots you could have if this was a pay up front 60 dollar game so where the free to play model loses me is where it costs more in the long run to get the same amount of gameplay from a free to play game versus a pay to play game luckily any decent player can earn additional slots by trading uncommon and rare items found ingame but you wont need to constantly buy slots you get your weapons very slowly anyway most weapons have to be crafted and after you grind the needed ingredients the weapon takes 12 to 24 hours to assemble my biggest complaint lies in the current mechanics of kubrows while playing youll get a quest to get a space dog bat thing to assist you in combat when you pay out the nose for the required blueprints grind the materials grind more money to make the items grind until you get an egg wait 4 to 5 days for the thing to mature you will be rewarded with a companion that literally slowly dies no you read that correctly while it sits in your spaceship your space doggity will slowly die and the only way to reverse this is to buy health injectors for 75000 credits for a six pack this is nothing short of space highway robbery most players who find this out immediately regret getting the dog thing and when a majority of players regret a gameplay element you know something has gone horribly wrong the worst part is they also sell robot companions that are armed with guns dont require upkeep and cost less in the long run it really hangs a giant question mark over the point of owning a batdog this isnt the only poorlyreceived mechanic sometimes youll attract the mark of an ai controlled bounty hunter by killing a highvalue target they have a slim chance to show up in the middle of one of your missions and fight you this sounds good on paper but in order to even have a chance against them you need to have multiple high level players with maxed out weapons with very specific kinds of damage it turns what could have been a thrilling raid boss into an arbitrary mission failure most of the time so yes play this game play through the prologue and if youre liking what you see so far continue playing it if you can do the following  ditch your space doggity in cryo sleep  pretend the bounty hunters do not exist just alt  f4 your game when they show up and you have no possible way of combating them  find reliable friends to help you with the most difficult mission modes and events  seriously the bounty hunters will just ruin your fun 90% of the time when you get ingame emails from them just hit the delete button while making a dismissive farting noise  handle the grind yes theres going to be grind but at least its more fun than most
