developer to be purchased by perfect world entertainment i do not recommend this game if that is that case avoid it gameplay a the main attraction its got fastpaced gunplay and swordplay mixed in with parkour and scifi eviscerate your enemys in violent bloody explosions and shoot guys legs off or chop them straight in half with your sword  warframe is a hell of a lot of fun but the downside to it right now is the repetitive stages and missions theres still a lot of bugs right now but this is excusable because this game is still in beta story not much of one currently not much going on in the story department right now for warframe all you really know is that youve been woken up from cryostasis to fight these guys called the grineer and these other guys known as the corpus so you just wake up and start slaughtering literally hundreds of people because some lady with a funny hat told you to more recently theyve begun doing more story related events and improving on this aspect of the game so theres probably something to look forward to in that regard crafting its ok but there are restrictions a little overwhelming to new players because crafting looks and seems like its impossible but once you start putting some time into wiki and unlocking stages it becomes simple to find the right resources and craft the weapons and warframes you want just set a goal for yourself play and youll have the items you desire at no cost except for some time and effort the wait time for crafting in warframe is a huge turn off when youre a brand new player because youre itching to get away from the god awful starter gear and onto something more fun so that can be quite frustrating but later on once youve actually got some stuff for yourself made and youre more comfortable with your gear the crafting wait becomes more exciting you start to look forward to the completion of your new gear once theyre finished and while those are building you start hunting for more resources to make the next thing on your list the biggest mistake in this game is limiting the number of items you can have and only letting you get more space by spending real world money  this is  and you should be able to use your credits to purchase more inventory slots if it werent for this id have given this system a thumbs up clans time consuming but very rewarding clans are sort of like the hidden second half of the game start a clan to work on building up your dojo with some friends its a lot of fun you have more things to work towards and gives you more reasons to actually do missions for materials other than making guns and armor  youll be able to access weapons and research not avaliable from the basic store pages visuals stunning in most right places very lackluster in others the corpus ships are gleaming and sleek while the grineer ships are grimey and industrial with dim lighting void ships are decorated in shining gold with flawless white walls and have glass pipelines with flowing water in them that you can see into but the desert tileset is extremely ugly and the game uses a random color correction filter to try and make the stages seem a little different each time but they end up just making the stages look strange and unfit most of the time the character models are packed with detail and the weapons are sexy however if you want to customize your warframe with a full color wheel youll have to dish out some cash and unlock them with platnum music nothing special the music in warframe is inspired by japanese drums and thats about it just drums and some metal clanking hopefully the game gets a real soundtrack someday will update review as the game gets updates
