warframe is a fast paced third person action shooter with decent rpg and adventure elements mixed in to create a very very enjoyable free to play experience i cannot fit every aspect of this game into this review so i will be highlighting what are in my opinion the most important key features of the game the general plot and setting of this game takes place in a scifi themed perspective of our solar system in the distant future where two factions the corpus and the grineer compete for territory and power while avoiding hazards like outbreaks from the infestation and tenno intervention the world is ever changing maps you play are procedurally generated with different tile sets and themes depending on what planet youre based around the corpus and grineer are constantly invading each others territory allowing players to pick sides and decide who will occupy that territory until the opposing faction is ready to invade again infestation constantly plague regions of the galaxy allowing tenno to help thwart them with enemy factions for the greater good warframe offers a very fast paced smooth yet gritty and meaty combat system players are able to find a wide assortment of weapons warframes and abilities to play the way they want to play ranging from being a stealthy hunter able to execute your enemies from behind cloak and dagger style sneak through patrolling squads to quickly reach your targets without sounding the alarm or test your bowmanship or sniper skills picking off enemies from afar or charge in guns and swords blazing dismembering anything that stands between you and your assignment and you think support classes in most games are boring warframes support and utility classes offer very fun abilities and play styles that not only give the player an enjoyable experience but greatly help out your team or offer for very leisurely solo gameplay on top of combat movement in this game is one of the best in the genre often joked for being a game about space ninjas you will find yourself running along and up walls leaping and flipping through the air over and on top of the enemy and sliding about skillfully through levels making traveling something to actually look forward to weapons warframes sentinels and miscellaneous gear are obtained through a very fair and balanced crafting system blueprints are obtained by purchasing them in the ingame shop for ingame currency or found through various mission styles while the materials are obtained through different areas in the solar system while many pieces of equipment are available to buy through microtransactions almost everything can be crafted in game with the exception of a few cosmetic items and discontinued event items the game is designed to allow players any type of experience they want whether you want to play alone or with up to 3 other people although certain level types are obviously easier with a friend or two almost everything can be done alone and difficulty will scale to your current gears progress one thing i find is a double edged sword with the current game is level design the game is primarily procedurally generated with preexisting rooms arranged in different orders and different themes depending on the levels location in the solar system while the tile sets themselves are very well designed you will find yourself going through the same rooms over and over again throughout different missions and sometimes within the same level however because of how fast paced the game is it is not an issue for most players and does not affect gameplay whatsoever from what ive seen and experienced there are only two very minor vices to this game microtransactions and clans platinum is a currency that can be purchased by players to either buy gear or cosmetic items however warframes and weapons themselves cost ridiculously high amounts of platinum encouraging players to craft them from scratch in game which may be time consuming but isnt difficult in most cases additionally prime gear and other alertevent related items are not purchasable and using microtransactions will not necessarily give players an advantage over their friends one of the main reasons i personally buy platinum is for cosmetics like custom color palettes and aesthetic attachments for weapons warframes and sentinels however considering how much content you get in this game for absolutely free i would argue that they are more than worth investing a little bit of change into if cosmetics are something you enjoy in games the other issue although not nearly as significant would be clans specific warframes weapons and other gear are only obtainable through clan system crafting in the dojo which forces players to join one if they want to have access to all the content however you can get away with having a personal clan or with a couple friends as research and crafting scale to clan size one of the things that stands out to me the most for warframe as an mmo is the developers and the community as an overall it is extremely community driven and the developers are closely closely involved with their game adding hotfixes for big and minor issues almost daily to ensure the best experience for players new content is added almost weekly and large scale events happen every month or so something pretty insignificant that i make a big deal out of is that the in game developer messages for patches or hotfixes are absolutely hilarious and they do listen and respond to general chat channels often warframe is definitely worth investing some time into i have yet to find a freetoplay game that offers as much content as this game without pressuring microtransations the combat style is extremely unique and fast paced and allows players to play exactly the way they want to good luck tenno
