i first tried out this game a long long time ago during the beta as a founder the money i spent for the founder pack is something i have yet to regret every new patch brings new features more diversity in the missions new frames and very often new zones even if it is free to play there is no need to spend a lot of money on this game im still running on my original founders platinum which ive mostly used to buy more slots for my warframeweapons as well as a few cosmetic itemsthe crafting is very well done and offers a wide range of possibilities and a good alternative to spending platinum to buy gear and frames for casual players with only a few hours to invest in a game you can have fun with this only playing a few hours a week for the more hardcore players you can spend an easy 200 hours probably more to get everything and upgrade everything the major downside of this game is the social aspect unlike other arpgs the fast paste gameplay makes it harder to socialize than in other arpgs the clan system is pretty nice and the general chat offers good alternative for socialising but as a whole i feel the game is not quite there yet and i am convinced they are working on improving that aspect somehow the game devs are really there with the community and participate in eventsinteract with the players a lot its really fun to see so much enthusiasm in todays gaming world all in all ill start playing the game and tell myself just a few runs ill only be on for an hour or so but then i spend 34 hours running stuff and realise that well its 5 am and i should probably go to bed because i have work in 3 hours s as a founder i highly recommend this game to anyone who enjoys arpgs crafting farming and participating in event
