ive read a bunch of the negative reveiws and most are people who dont know how to play the game right so heres a list of solutions to all that stuff problem rng dependent progression solution dont transmute mods unless they are low quality rare mods are actually valuable so there cant be a surefire way to get them otherwise the game would have no content problem too much farming solution stop trying to farm for highend items right off the bat you actually have to look at what resources you have access to and choose your next weaponwarframe from there in most games you find the weapon you want then farm what you need here its actually a challenge to get stuff problem stuff never drops solution do something else on the same planet and after no time youll have what you need if youre looking for a more rare resource do an assassination they are garunteed to drop at least one of their planets rarest resource so its more reliable than just hoping it will pop out of a basic enemy problem endgame takes forever solution this game is not for people who want to buy a game play for an hour or two then have every item that ever existed this game actually gives a challenge in getting items theyre worth a lot more than people think problem mods too rare solution thats because theyre worth something they provide more advancement than just getting the next weapon in fact they are about as rare as weapons in other games you just have to get over the fact that theyre powerful and you dont get them every two seconds also mod farming is incredibly inefficient just find something else to do and they will come faster than you think if you have a theifs wit mod you probably do theyre incredibly common then dont throw it away it makes getting mods a million times easier problem pay to win solution stop trying to buy youre way to endgame thats not where the content is also prime weapons can be built like any other and they mostly have the same stats as the normal version but with different mod polarities its also somewhat of an accomplishment to build one so its sort of a show of your prestige at the game problem overpriced platinum solution yet again all the items are worth more than you probably think the prices match the gameplay it would take to build the item so theyre actually pretty fair and the only things that cost a lot are weapons and warframes which are more fun to build anyway problem monotonous missions solution play different missions farming the same thing may seem efficient but its just going to make you think thats all there is problem math solution oh im sorry i didnt realize using basic multiplication to compare two things is so hard thats really too much for you to handle overall this is a great game it does take awhile to get stuff but thats because its not meant to be completed the idea is that not all of the content is locked off till you reach endgame its distributed throughout the progression of game so items are valuable yet not impossible to obtain at every stage of the game youll love it as long as you dont expect to become grand champion of the universe a day after you play it
recommended
the game is incredibly fun but has some issues with a handful of mechanics here and there it very much relies on the well its still technically in beta excuse that being said it is sometimes a valid excuse sometimes content updates can seem few and far between and other times it seems like they release update after update within a few days that being said they tend to fix things that are broken even if it does take them some time while i do not agree with all of the creative paths they have chosen to take the community has responded very well to it really bringing lifeblood to the game despite all of this warframe achieves the simplest need for any game to be fun it has a lot going for it and the developers really care about their product and they both care that people enjoy it as much as they need it for profits that being said the freemium incentives can be a bit much ingame you can play the entire game freetoplay but there are times where if you really want to enjoy the game you have to spend money the simplest example of this is inventory slots you are limited to a certain number at the beginning of the game and more can only be obtained through purchase using realworld currency equivalents that being said i tend to find the thought well its okay these developers deserve my money for the amazing product they have provided floating through my head just be careful not to go overboard the game is worth an initial cash purchase of $20$40 but no game is worth the hundreds some people are willing to sink into the game despite some of the negativity in this review i have to give the game an overallpositive thumbs up this is just because the game is so damn fun the parkour is entertaining if a bit buggy at times which only adds to the hilarity the combat is effective and you feel like you have an impact if appropriately leveled archwing has grown on me somewhat if still a bit lacking in my opinion dont get me wrong its great but i earnestly believe it didnt need to be in the game the weapon and character varieties keep the game spicy and customization is off the charts the one tip i have to you concerning this game dont play too much youll burn yourself out immediately and it can get very depressing to wait ingame for something to construct oh i suppose i should mention that too before this review is over crafting an item and often times the pieces for that item as well can take hours it takes 25 missions for individual resources depending on the complexity of the item and the rarity of the resource and then you set the item up to build in the foundry which can take hours no im not exaggerating most characters called warframes take about 12 hours to build each individual part helmet suit and systems though they can all be worked on simultaneously plus 3 days to combine the three together i despise the amount that this incentivizes the freemium model for collecters like myself but i will admit its satisfying when its done what was i saying oh right burning yourself out the reason i mention the foundry is because within the first few months of play i started to feel overwhelmed with grinding and waiting and i was doing the parts of the game i hated while waiting for the parts i wanted which made the parts i wanted feel disappointing the game is fun but recognize which parts of the game you like and dont play the parts you hate to the point of upset i suppose most people should take this for granted but you may find yourself just too damn addicted to the game if this happens back off put the game down for a few days ignore the login rewards they get disappointing after a while then come back a week later the game will seem as fresh new and fun as it did within your first week of play overall the game has its issues and while it hasnt overcome all of its issues yet the amount of fun the game provides is well worth it buy play this game
