first things first  this game does look attractive  if you ignore the fact that the character models look like theyre concept art or something secondly  i did have trouble getting my head around the game the ingame tutorial is lacking and often leaves you confused about what to do next it took me quite a long time to figure out the nature of the polarity slots  by spending several hours and days on warframewiki to try and make sense of everything  which you will also be doing at some point thirdly  the quest system is completely backwards imagine if you will a quest line in any other game one quest leads you to a new quest etc etc well in warframe the first quest is simple but then youre given quests that are rediculously hard to achieve at first because you need to grind for parts of a machine that you havent even built yet because that takes 72 hours and then build the thing so in a sense youre on a quest to collect parts for a machine and when you get them you have to wait 72 hours to actually do the quest its pathetic this waiting time is forced upon you by the developers to make money so they deliberately make the game a waiting game you can either sit around for 72 hours before progressing further  or you can pay fourthly  repetitiveness youll soon come to terms with the fact that this game is a grind fest if you like grinding  youll love warframe but even that does have a cracking point allinall the game does have its flaws but it is attractive and enjoyable to play the abilities of certain classes are awesome to use but youll have to farm repetitively for parts of that class in order to be able to build that class which has a waiting time remember before you can play that class are you seeing where this is going if you enjoy nonsensical violence and enjoy exercising your patience then this is for you
