warframe has got to be one of my most favorite games of all time and it still as the developers want to say hasnt fully released despite having enough content to make three games not only is warframe free but its also updated often and has quite a lot of replayability pros 1 warframes a warframe is an exosuit designed for your tenno which is basically the entire point of the game and is even its name you start off the game by picking one of three frames excalibur loki and volt before proceeding through the tutorial mission and selecting your beginner weapons as you go through the game there will be a massive collection of warframes to collect with their own unique powers and stats some of which are passive like mesas health bonus if you dont take a melee weapon into battle or zephyrs lowgravity these frames can be bought with platinum from the game store or crafted with blueprints purchased from the game store with credits some frames the only few so far being mesa limbo and mirage must be crafted through quests which take you through bits of the games story and missions to acquire pieces to the blueprints which you must craft similarly to the other warframes there are a total of twentytwo unique warframes not including their prime variations and all are a blast to acquire and use 2 weapons this game has a large variety of weapons and when i say large i mean borderlands 2large from pistols to snipers to a light machine gun from daggers to hammers to glaives to a literal gunsword there are at least one or two weapons released every few hotfixes and updates and if i bothered to count each individual weapon whether they were from events were primed versions or are from syndicates and tried to explain each one we could easily be here all night just looking over it all melee wepoans come with their own special mods which allows for melee combos and increased capacity to its mod points and add immensely to the level of gameplay in warframe each melee weapon type has its own individual stance mod there are twenty categories of melee weapons available for you to choose from and still growing with each update 3 mods mods in warframe allow you to increase stats on a weapon warframe sentinel or kubrow mods can even be sold in the player market for the games funbuckcurrency platinum or transmuted to create a new mod which a chance to get a rare mod these mods can be upgraded singularly to provide better benefits like 100% more damage or 70% more crit rate and the effectiveness of these mods depends on the weapons stats alone one weapon may benefit from a critrate mod more than others going from a 5% crit rate to 25% while another would only go from 2% to 5% due to it being meant for a different build this allows you to really look and see what fits best for a weapon to make it as effective as possible allowing you to do the math in your head to enter the battlefield with a literal monster in your hands the amount of mods you can put on a weapon are determined by the polarity or polarities of a weapon or warframe if the warframeweapon has an orokin reactorcatalyst installed and if the warframe has an aura mod installed or the weapon melee only has a stance mod installed aurastance mods provide extra points depending on the level of the mod itself and the polarity of the stance or aura slot matching a mod polarity to a slot polarity will greatly increase the number of points it gives you for aurastance mods or decrease the amount of points it uses for basic mods 4 platinum now for a touchy subject with every freetoplay game the premium currency platinum warframe in my personal opinion gets this bit right in the best possible way platinum is very expensive and for all the right reasons this is because they allow you to immediately purchase special resources weapons cosmetics or even entire warframes the frames and weapons coming with their respective orokin catalysts or reactors as well as an inventory slot there are few things that can only be achieved through platinum the most important being warframe slots and weapon slots which can be recieved by doing events which give free weapons inviting enough friends into the game purchasing premium or prime access directly or trading some ingame goodies with other players for platinum these goodies could be rare maxranked mods for weapons or even prime parts earned from the void that you can get for simply playing the game long enough there is no such thing as pay to win in warframe especially considering its marketed as a coop game if there is anything of the sorts like this its moreorless pay to get quicker and even then you could only pay 40 platinum to speed a weapons build time as opposed to buying the weapon for 250 platinum alone 5 grinding id like to make a note here that grinding is absolutely no reason to dislike a game as every game has grinding when you follow the definition we use in gaming grinding for exp grinding for money grinding for weapons or armor or whatever every game has potential for a grindfest and while warframe is subject to this a good majority of mmos and rpgs are as well cons i cant think of any other than the occasional bug that wont really be noticeable unless you look for it with the sole intention of pointing it out the developers dont really try to milk money out of you as much as they try to keep you playing the game but if i dont put something here someone will cry 1 rngesus as you would expect with just about any game the system at which items are rewarded mostly pertaining to prime parts are at random since prime parts can only be obtained from void missions or trading platinum for it and since there is such a whopping large majority of prime weapons and warframes this means that you could spend a week of grinding through void missions for parts you want to build a prime weapon or prime warframe you want example overall id give this game a 95 out of 10 and id recommend it to anyone looking to get into a shooter
