warframe is a coop based thirdperson shooter set in a futuristic universe where you play as the tenno a race of reawakened warriors that are sustained in these suits called warframes and begin clearing out the solar system of threats such as the grineer a race of xenophobic clones that hate everything thats not a grineer including the tenno then you have corpus a unified profit organisation that seeks to make profit and kill everything that stops them from making profit and then you have infestations that are organic lifeforms that seek to spread and infect the solar system warframe is one of the most polished f2p games ive ever played and heres why the gameplay is fastpaced fun and overall just awesome i love slicing and dicing and pinning my foes to the wall the different warframes you have which are the suits the tenno you wear add many ways to playing you have a wide range of weapons to use as well which ill list below swords pistols assault rifles axes staffs hammers shotguns bows crossbows sniper rifles rocket launchers revolvers machine pistols also you have sentinels and kubrow which are companions that act as a support role that help you during missions there are different types of sentinels and kubrows that have different stats and abilities so in that sense youd pick the one that suits your playstyle outside of missions youre on your ship even though when this game came out it was just a menu screen you had the ship feature came in later anyway you have your navigation system which lets you select which planet you wanna go to and do some missions youll also get daily events which you receive rewards for completing you have other components on the ship like the foundry for crafting the arsenal for all your equipment the comms for additional features the mods segment for combining and upgrading mods and the incubator for keeping your kubrow in graphically speaking its a very good looking game especially for f2p standards the particle effects the lighting the colors the overall attention to detail is impressive the aesthetic of warframes universe is very flashy very colorful and very pretty sound is pretty good too music is alright weapon sound ambient noise and the voice acting is pretty solid as for story usually most f2p games dont really interest me in the story aspect or atleast i hadnt found one yet but this game gets pretty interesting when you start digging up the lore from the codexes wiki pages or even forums or videos that delve into the mythos of warframe its good so far but it still needs to be more fleshed out and built upon more what i gave on the first paragraph was really just the background story a brief and very basic explanation of what warframes about and what youre doing warframe is like i said a coop game you do have the option to play on your own but unless youre equipped to do so youre better off grouping with friends or other people because thats when the experience is at its best in my opinion there is pvp despite it not being the main focus of the game i personally havent touched it yet but maybe at some point i will all i know is that you can do 1v1 duels in the dojo and dark sector conflicts where clans fight for territory but still the addition of pvp is a good thing regardless it adds more replay value to the game itself warframe is one of the few games in the f2p market thats not necessarily p2w alot of the things you get in the market you can craft without ever spending a dime in the game credits are your main currency and is what lets you buy some weapons that allow you to pay with credits blueprints which lets you craft things from warframes weapons items etc platinum is a currency that you aquire by using your money to buy things outright instead of crafting them but like i stated you dont have to spend money to get anywhere in this game you can get almost everything from crafting whilst it may take longer in the end youll still have that item you want ever since warframes release the game has been getting better and better with new updates new weapons new warframes new events etc theres always a reason to go back and the regular updates and its great gameplay is one of the reasons why this game is so popular recently the archwing update came which brought in space combat which is a huge stepup in the progression of developing this game further hell maybe at one point they might even allow you to literally fly your ship around the solar system and not just walk in it in the end you have one of the best f2p games in recent memory that has a strong developement team digital extreme that constantly improves the game a big community and a fair f2p model yes it is grindy yes it is repetitive but it is also rewarding and fun at the same time
