warframe was a different game for me i usually dont play online third person shooters or any online shooter for that matter the game had a interesting setup i liked the fact that this game has a lot of customization on weapons however the game has quite a few issues first of all this game is heavy pay to win crafting in this game takes a lot of time 12 hours for weapons and a lot of credits in game currency however people who pay for the game can just buy these weapons from the start people who pay can also buy additional warframes from the start which have to be crafted it is very difficult to do by non paying members non paying members are also limited in even the basic colors of their warframe they are only given a tiny fraction of colors that didnt include black which bothered me since its one of my favorite colors that are honestly not that good with the exception of a few as for gameplay itself it seemed to have good mechanics i liked the fact that you can beat a level with stealth to avoid fighting masses of enemies best done solo with loki warframe weapon balance seemed good combat is fast paced fluid and full of action live action and several different ways to use melee attacks along with awesome jumps had me at times just messing around with the controls for fun the game feels kind of disconnected between players though throughout my time playing this game very few players would talk to me and honestly there wasnt much to talk about the game also has very repetetive maps while i understand making a unique map for every single level would be impossible throughout my time playing i only saw three maps an underground cave a base on a icy planet and a warship the individual sections are also repetitive by one or two playthroughs of each map you will have seen almost every section there is it would be nice to see a unique design for every world which i think is possible the missions themselves are highly repetative i found myself doing the same thing over and over again with few alterations some new mission types should be added to the game to curb its repetetive feel in the end if you are going to play this game as a dedicated player be ready to fork out some money because my f2p run of this game had me leaving by the time i finished mars some improvments that i think would help the game create at least three unique maps for each world get a world chat lobby to connect the players a little more make demos for weapons so we know what the gun is like before we go through the trouble of getting them and add some new missions to make the game less repetetive well there is my review
