warframe is a bit of an enigma in the free to play market as it is very different from most other free to play games so instead of rating it the way i usually do im going to list the pros and cons and you can decide for yourself pros very polished gameplay and mechanics a large variety of frames and weapons leading to many styles of gameplay with new ones being added on a roughly monthly basis very indepth customization ive yet to see 2 frames with the exact same color scheme built in alertinvasion system for bonus rewards so the game doesnt get boring built in high difficulty setting for missions youve already cleared so lower level missions are still worth coming back to seasonal events that shake things up a bit constant stream of rewards from doing missions generally nice community cons some frames are really hard to get if you dont pay eg components are bound to random alerts etc there are a few balancing issues making some frames and weapons far superior to others limited warframe slots if you dont buy more 2 by default game hits a slight difficulty wall around jupiter missions and beyond if you dont have an orokin reactor starting weapons are terrible get others as soon as you can some items seem a little highly priced for you get ex $5 for a new color palette environments can get a little repeatative after a while other notes things that could be a pro or con depending on your preferance and are worth mentioning pvp almost nonexistant 90% of the game is pve generally not advised to play solo and will get the most fun out of it with friends has trading system but is very limited damage system is fairly complex and deep may be confusing to some a little grindy to get some items but if you have a fair amount of patience shouldnt be too bad no dedicated servers game just picks the best host and starts and thats the gist of warframe if youre on the fence give it a try its free to play
