recommended
if youre looking for a time sink youve come to the right place a rather interesting game in the already hypersaturated freetoplay shooter genre i personally enjoy the various mechanics and the iterative fundamental gameplay changes the developers continue to roll out every few weeks just be aware that if you like this game expect to spend massive amounts of time grinding through semirepetitive situations it is actually completely possible to progress in this game with the freetoplay model as the games scalingprogressive content is influenced by the number of missions that you do and you can get ingame money for upgrades by trading valuable blueprintsmods to other players though the game seems to push that this is all about space ninjas i think its better to describe this game as a thirdperson mobile shooting gallery as enemy ai is very basic and your ranged weapons have the most effective damage throughout all stages of the game the most recent update u13 introduced melee 20 which greatly boosted the effectiveness of melee weaponry though that being said only a small handful of weapons are effective at all in the late game would i recommend this to my friends no too much time of mine has been wasted shooting and cutting millions of enemies to ribbons i do not exactly regret that time but i worry that anyone else who plays it may find their time consumed very quickly would i recommend this to anyone else absolutely its a grindfest with enjoyable replayability and a broad spectrum of content to satisfy your tastes i find the game relaxing most of the time that being said the game really isnt intended to be that way and from what i gather new players have a very difficult time getting used to various mechanics enemy types and advancing in the game best way to start find a friend whos experienced have them carry you through a few missions to help you get some advanced materials playing the game with friends is quite a lot more enjoyable than with pubs i look forward to the future of this game and i sincerely enjoy participating in its continual evolution
